<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    {{>header}}
    <div class="main-content">
        
        <h1 class="main-title">About This App</h1>
        <div class="weather-card">
            <p>
                This weather application was built as a learning project to explore
            full-stack JavaScript development using Node.js.
            </p>

            <p>
                Users can search for a city or location and receive current weather conditions in either Fahrenheit or Celsius.
            </p>

            <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Node.js & Express</li>
                <li>Weatherstack API</li>
                <li>Mapbox Geocoding API</li>
                <li>HTML, CSS, and Client-Side JavaScript</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>What I Learned</h2>
            <p>
                This project helped me gain experience working with APIs, handling
                asynchronous callbacks, managing query parameters, and building
                responsive user interfaces.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
    
    {{>footer}}
</body>
</html>